name: Otis Chandler
about:
I'm the Co-Founder of Goodreads, and am really enjoying seeing my friends (and millions of people around the world) use it. I've loved to read since the second grade when I discovered the Hardy Boys. Lately I like good business books, biographies of famous people, and the occasional sci-fi or classic fiction book.

The value I get out of Goodreads is that it helps me read more. What gets a person excited to read a book is when they have a strong recommendation. Recommendations from friends are the best, but we don't always have the luxury of having those, so we've built a community of book readers and a top-notch algorithmic recommendation engine to help people find their next favorite read.

I love books, and I believe more than anything in the power of storytelling to change and improve our lives.

name: Douglas
about:
I am a business finance guy now in residential real estate with big ambitions and a strong drive to succeed.

I started a regimen in 2005 to read two books per month. That has compounded to the growing list you see here. During that time, I have found that reading is a great way to broaden my understanding in a variety of areas. Though my principal focus is real estate, stock selection, stuff about .com's, and personal improvement, I have realized that reading books outside of that area helps me connect better with people. Not to mention take me to a place far from what I know here in the states.

I have also started to learn to like biographies because when things are tough, reading about the path of many public figures helps put my situation in proper perspective.

Send me an email. I would love to hear your commentary and advice.

A yearly log of my book reading:
2005: 24
2006: 12
2007: 25
2008: 32
2009: 36 - 5 real estate inv books
2010: 20 - 1 real estate inv book
2011: 7

name: Courtney
about:
life is fabulous. i am passionate about juan, friends, family, vino, reading reading reading, living in the pacific northwest, hiking, my puppies, legal issues, silence, dry humor, original ideas, showtunes, babies, star jasmine, the outdoors, indie music, concerts, scary movies, yellow cake with chocolate frosting, musicals, words, the smell of library books, and lavender...i could go on and on. i'm not sentimental and tend to be forward-thinking (despite my puppy/baby/showtune thing). i dislike tchotchkes, artifical light, romantic comedies, and small-minded people (among other things and in no particular order).

I have been an avid reader my entire life, and I read all the time - usually a couple of books a week, in addition to tons of work-related reading (I'm a lawyer). I was one of those kids who could be bribed to do pretty much anything for a book - I remember my mother once cajoled me into getting a bowl cut by promising to buy me a new book (sad but true story - proof in pictures). Reading was, is, and will always be an enjoyable and necessary activity.

name: Suzanne
about:
I am an elder woman who teaches classes in womens' spirituality, as well as meditation and spiritual healing for beginners. I have been a spiritual teacher and healer for 35+ years.

I love to read. I find high-quality writing inspiring in any genre. Except for writing on topics related to crime or violence or war. I avoid those. I am not interested in reading about human misery, no matter how well characters triumph over it.

I especially enjoy reading and sharing well-written books for young children. My favorite children's book author is Charlotte Zolotow. Old-fashioned, I know. But, as a good friend of mine says, you know it's good children's literature when everyone in the group is transfixed at story time. And that's what happens with Ms. Zolotow.
